sqldiff.help:
USE: The diffs are ordered by datamodel version number. The script can be run in a top down fashion and is expected to not fail or overwrite old data
EXPECT: - "use business-database-name;" was called prior to calling this script

diff.author: Tammy Dugan
diff.description: Added mapping for PSF_rescan state that creates a new PWS.
diff.sql: INSERT INTO chirdlutilbackports_state_mapping (`initial_state`, `next_state`,`program_id`) select max(a.state_id),max(b.state_id),max(program_id) from chirdlutilbackports_state a,chirdlutilbackports_state b, chirdlutilbackports_program c where a.name='PSF_rescan' and b.name='QUERY KITE PWS' and c.name='chica';

diff.author: Meena Sheley
diff.description: Adding encounter types for manual checkins and hl7 checkins if the encounter_types do not already exist in the table
diff.sql:
INSERT into encounter_type (name, description, creator, date_created, uuid) (select distinct 'HL7Message','Arrival from HL7 message', 1, NOW(), UUID() from encounter_type WHERE 'HL7Message' NOT IN (SELECT name FROM encounter_type where name = 'HL7Message'));
INSERT into encounter_type (name, description, creator, date_created, uuid) (select distinct 'ManualCheckin','Patient checked in manually', 1, NOW(), UUID() from encounter_type WHERE 'ManualCheckin' NOT IN (SELECT name FROM encounter_type where name = 'ManualCheckin'));

diff.author: Vibha Anand

diff.sql: UPDATE `encounter_type` set retired = 0 where name='ManualCheckin' or name='HL7Message'

diff.author: Vibha Anand
diff.description: Added a Cron job to update the voided column of user who is a provider and is inactive.
diff.sql: INSERT INTO scheduler_task_config (`name`, `schedulable_class`, `start_time`, `start_time_pattern`, `repeat_interval`, `start_on_startup`, `started`, `created_by`, `date_created`, `uuid`) select 'Cron job retiring Inactive Providers', 'org.openmrs.module.chica.ChicaProvidersCron', NOW(), 'MM/dd/yyyy HH:mm:ss',86400, 1, 0, 1, NOW(), UUID() from (select count(*) as cnt from scheduler_task_config where name='Cron job retiring Inactive Providers') a where a.cnt=0;
